3. Is there a natural approach to Psoriasis?

Psoriasis is a chronic skin condition in which the skin
cells divide many times faster than normal, the result is
discomforting and unsightly pileup of skin cells. The
lesions appear red and inflamed and are often covered
with silvery scales. There is no real medical "cure" for
psoriasis. Medically this condition is treated at the point
of lesion, when in fact this condition is usually a body
problem and the skin is really a mirror of what is going
on inside of the body. With skin conditions it is important
to remember the skin is an organ of elimination. It allows
waste material that can't escape from other body organs
of elimination to come out through the all-encompassing
envelope of the body. Natural therapies to consider
would include detoxification, colon cleansing, Nutrition
therapy with, vitamin A, zinc, vitamin E, and selenium.
Researchers in England found that psoriasis patients who
took ten fish-oil capsules a day for eight weeks greatly
reduced their symptoms of itching, redness, and scaling.
My feeling about this whole problem is to first use a
detoxification program for the intestinal area and then
the liver to clean out the body waste. Especially if you
have an arthritic condition with the psoriasis skin condition,
then use a comprehensive nutritional support program to
maintain and improve your level of internal body health
to stop the problem from returning.

