Allergies are a major problem for millions of people
today. When one person has so many I would look at
you digestive processes, intestinal function, and liver.
Here's why, if you're not digesting properly food can
get to the blood stream in a larger than normal molecular
size, it will actually act as a foreign body, causing an
antigen antibody reaction to occur - the outcome is an
allergic response in your body. If you are not digesting
properly, undigested food will stay in the gut too long.
Over a period of time, the gut lining will become more
porous than normal and allow more waste food to spill
through the gut lining. This will overload the liver
detoxification processes, causing increased waste to
circulate through the body or to be deposited in the
body, to cause problems at a later time. The liver is
your largest organ of detoxification, but it has certain
